data.database_description: This database schema is designed to manage academic records and operations within an educational institution. It includes tables for classrooms, departments, courses, instructors, sections, student enrollments, advisors, time slots, and course prerequisites. The schema supports tracking of course offerings, instructor schedules, student grades, and departmental budgets, facilitating comprehensive management of educational activities and resources.

columns.columnDescription: The name of the building where the classroom is located.
The number of the room within the building.
The maximum number of students that can be accommodated in the classroom.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about classrooms in the institution.

columns.columnDescription: Unique name of each department.
Location of the department's building.
Budget allocated to the department.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about departments within the institution.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each course.
Title of the course.
Name of the department offering the course.
Number of credits awarded for completing the course.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about courses offered by the institution.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each instructor.
Name of the instructor.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about instructors within the educational institution.

columns.columnDescription: The unique identifier for the course.
The unique identifier for the section within a course.
The semester in which the section is offered (e.g., Fall, Spring).
The year in which the section is offered.
The name of the building where the section is held.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a specific time slot.
The day of the week on which the time slot occurs (e.g., M, T, W, Th, F).
